<subSubSection id="02C66578FFE2FFA3FC959E136AF67E51" pageId="15" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FC959E136AF77FEE" blockId="15.[831,1437,599,816]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FC959E136ABD7F0E" bold="true" box="[831,944,599,623]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Remarks:</emphasis>
The test diameter increases rapidly towards the apertural end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFE2FFA3FC959ED36AF67E51" blockId="15.[831,1437,599,816]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFE2FFA3FC959ED36D707FCE" bold="true" box="[831,1149,663,687]" pageId="15" pageNumber="29">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene but its range may be extended to Early Eocene (LE ROY, 1953). In the study area, it is found in the Campanian, Maastrichtian and Paleocene Zones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
